China Stocks: Jinan Truck, Sanjing Pharmaceutical, Pangang

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-02-16T02:18:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/china-stocks-jinan-truck-sanjing-pharmaceutical-pangang.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  China  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses as of 9:57 a.m. local time local time.  The Shanghai Composite Index, which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, fell 3.4, or 0.1 percent, to 2,895.83.
The  CSI 300 Index  gained 0.1 percent to 3,219.2.  CNHTC Jinan Truck Co. (000951 CH), the listed unit of the
country’s largest heavy truck producer, rose 5.1 percent to
28.06 yuan after saying sales volume rose 74 percent in January
from a year ago to 7,892 units.  Harbin Pharmaceutical Group Sanjing Pharmaceutical Co.
(600829 CH) jumped the 10 percent daily limit to 23.30 yuan.
Affiliate Harbin Pharmaceutical Group Co. (600664 CH) said it
plans to raise its stake in Sanjing Pharmaceutical to 74.8
percent from 30 percent currently and acquire 100 percent of a
bioengineering company from the parent company through a share
swap valued at a 5.7 billion yuan ($864.9 million). Harbin
Pharmaceutical Group Co. added 0.6 percent to 22.7 yuan. Both
stocks resumed trading after suspensions starting Dec. 29.       Pangang Group Steel Vanadium & Titanium Co. (000629 CH)
climbed 4.8 percent to 12.84 yuan. The steelmaker said
Australia’s Foreign Investment Review Board has approved an
asset swap plan with parent Angang New Co.  --Zhang Shidong. Editor: Reinie Booysen  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
